snippet.textDisplay:
Nice work orange clown, for putting more American lives in danger just so you can divert the heat of your impeachment away from you.

The idea of launching military action to distract from domestic political troubles has been a thing at least since the 1997 film “Wag the Dog” (as in, the tail wagging the dog) gave it a name. Republicans accused President Bill Clinton of it in 1998 when he ordered airstrikes against Sudan and Iraq as impeachment loomed.

In Trump words: I want them to hold my impeachment trial because I’m busy fighting the war I just started.
